author: sokra
message:
Turbopack: only enable nested async availability in production (#85728)

### What?

Adds a new mode for processing async imports (e. g. `import("...")`).

* Nested async chunking (the existing mode): Each async import creates a new availability scope so already available modules are not included again. This leads to exploring all paths in the application to create the most efficient chunk groups. The time complexity grows with the number of paths.
* Flat async chunking: Only the first async import creates a new availability scope. This makes all async imports have the same available modules (per page), no matter how deep their are nested in the application. This allows to reuse chunk groups. The time complexity is linear to the number of async imports.

The nested async chunking has a benefit when download size matters. Flat async chunking has better compile time and often less total bundle size. Therefore nested async chunking is only enabled in production for client-side assets.
